Company Overview of Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Health Care Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Health Care Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched by The Vanguard Group, Inc. It is managed by Wellington Management Company LLP. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating in the health care sector including pharmaceutical firms, medical supply companies, and businesses that operate hospitals and other health care facilities. The fund invests in growth stocks of mid-cap and large-cap companies. It employs fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors like high-quality balance sheets, able management, and new product potential that ...
Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Health Care Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched by The Vanguard Group, Inc. It is managed by Wellington Management Company LLP. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating in the health care sector including pharmaceutical firms, medical supply companies, and businesses that operate hospitals and other health care facilities. The fund invests in growth stocks of mid-cap and large-cap companies. It employs fundamental analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors like high-quality balance sheets, able management, and new product potential that may lead to above-average growth in revenues, and earnings to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the MSCI ACWI Health Care Index, the Spliced Health Care Index, and the Global Health/Biotechnology Funds Average. Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Health Care Fund was formed on May 23, 1984 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


280 Congress StreetBoston, MA 02210United StatesFounded in 1984



