Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Energy Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 11:16 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Energy Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Energy Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by The Vanguard Group, Inc. It is co-managed by Wellington Management Company LLP. The fund invests in the public equity markets of countries across the globe. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating in the energy sector including companies involved in exploration, production, and transmission of energy or energy fuels, making and servicing of component products for such activities, energy research, and energy conservation. The fund invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations with a focus on large-cap and mid-cap companies. It employs a combination...
Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Energy Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by The Vanguard Group, Inc. It is co-managed by Wellington Management Company LLP. The fund invests in the public equity markets of countries across the globe. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating in the energy sector including companies involved in exploration, production, and transmission of energy or energy fuels, making and servicing of component products for such activities, energy research, and energy conservation. The fund invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations with a focus on large-cap and mid-cap companies. It employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis with a bottom-up stock picking approach focusing on factors like cash flow and asset valuations in addition to earnings valuations, financial prospects, the prices of the securities, the stock market, fundamentals and attractive valuation, capitalization, volatility, expected growth rates, and regional exposure, and the economy in general to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the MSCI ACWI Energy Index, the Standard & Poor's Energy Sector Index, the Spliced Energy Index, and the Global Natural Resources Funds Average. It employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. Vanguard Specialized Funds - Vanguard Energy Fund was formed on May 23, 1984 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


100 Vanguard BoulevardV26Malvern, PA 19355United StatesFounded in 1984



Phone: 610-669-1000

Fax: 610-669-6600

institutional.vanguard.com/VGApp/iip/site/institutional/investments/productoverview?fundId=0051







